      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOREBAR (5) couldn't get the job done as favourite when resuming but never stopped trying when beaten a neck at Coffs Harbour. Is sure to have come on from that and can go one better this time. FUNKY COLD MEDINA (2) only warmed late on debut then progressed nicely at his second outing when in the firing line before finishing third. Is open to further improvement third-up and is drawn to get all the favours. Big threat. HERE'S BEAU (3) was well supported on debut last start and turned in a solid effort to finish second at Murwillumbah. Has plenty of scope for improvement and is one of the obvious chances. EGYPTIAN LASS (9) finds it tough to break through but has efforts littered through her form that can be competitive. The 3kg gets her in light again.",
